HEADWORD: Eosaurus
<hw>E`o*sau"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'hw`s</grk> dawn + <grk>say^ros</grk> lizard.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct marine reptile from the coal
measures of Nova Scotia; -- so named because supposed to be of the
earliest known reptiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

